         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#roueche1993">
            <p>Row 4, The fortune of Phrontinos triumphs ! <note>or</note> (Place of) Phrontinos. The fortune of the cross triumphs !</p>
            <p>Row 12.i, The fortune of the Blues triumphs!</p>
            <p>Row 12.ii, Place of <seg cert="low">Spandios</seg>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
             
            <p>Row 4: The first translation would apply if the cross is a later addition; but if it is original, the second translation provides a standard Christian acclamation (compare <ref type="inscription" n="143" target="iAph080604"/> for a similar formula). Row 8.i: The middle line is very probably the number ιγ´, thirteen; compare F.6.ii. Row 11: On the westernmost seat, the letters IB (<height>0.07</height>) may well be a number, 12: compare <ref type="inscription" n="764" target="iAph080058"/>.6.ii, and <ref type="inscription" n="765" target="iAph080059"/>.8. The letters below are much larger (<height>0.15–0.20</height>) and probably from κατ[έχεται].</p>
         </div>
